My First R Markdown

Introduction

Markdown is a very basic and easy-to-use syntax for styling written documents. Its very easy to make some words bold and other words italic with Markdown. You can even link to FCSIT!

Here is a code chunk and it prints the code and result.

set.seed(1)
x <- rnorm(100)
mean(x)
## [1] 0.1088874
